[% META
        title = "Production Database Migration to Kubernetes (Multi-Proxmox)"
   description = "Step-by-step plan for migrating 192.168.1.198 production database to Kubernetes cluster running across 3 Proxmox servers (proxmoxws, proxmox720, proxmoxt210) with load balancing and high availability"
   roles = "admin,developer,devops"
   TemplateType = "Documentation"
   category = "infrastructure,deployment,kubernetes"
   page_version = "1.5"
   last_updated = "Tue Dec 23 20:00:00 UTC 2025"
   site_specific = "false"
%]
[% PageVersion = 'root/Documentation/system/PRODUCTION_DB_KUBERNETES_MIGRATION_PLAN.tt,v 1.5 2025/12/23 zencoder Exp - Clarified dual-NIC architecture: each K8s VM on Proxmox LAN (192.168.1.x) + internal K8s bridge (192.168.123.x); added explicit delete/create commands for VMs 100,103,201,202 with cloud-init provisioning; documented access strategy (cloud-init setup, OpenVPN operations)' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Production Database Migration to Kubernetes</h1>
    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); font-size: 1.1em;"><strong>Migrate Bare-Metal 192.168.1.198 to Distributed K8s Cluster (Master on proxmoxws VM 100, Workers on proxmox720/proxmoxws)</strong></p>

    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
        Last Updated: 2025-12-23 |
        Version: 1.5 (Dual-NIC architecture + explicit delete/create commands) |
        Status: 📋 Implementation Planning - Ready for VM Rebuild |
        Scope: Migration of 192.168.1.198:3306 to K8s using dual-NIC setup (Proxmox LAN + K8s bridge), cloud-init provisioning, OpenVPN operations
    </div>

    <!-- INFRASTRUCTURE CLARIFICATIONS BANNER -->
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e9; border-left: 4px solid #2e7d32; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
        <h3 style="color: #1b5e20; margin-top: 0;">✅ Infrastructure Clarifications Incorporated (2025-12-23)</h3>
        <ul style="color: #2e7d32; font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 10px 0;">
            <li><strong>Q1 Answer</strong>: Production database is bare-metal server (192.168.1.198) outside Proxmox</li>
            <li><strong>Q2 Answer</strong>: VMID 1002 reserved for future Catalyst production (out of scope)</li>
            <li><strong>Q3 Answer</strong>: VMID 500 kept as disaster recovery backup (not needed for migration)</li>
            <li><strong>Q4 Answer</strong>: Use existing K8s nodes as-is (saves 2 weeks vs new cluster)</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #2e7d32; font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 10px 0;"><strong>Impact</strong>: Migration timeline optimized from 5-6 weeks to 2-3 weeks. Bare-metal database remains for production reliability. K8s cluster hosts application + dual-sync database mirror.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TABLE OF CONTENTS -->
    <div id="toc" class="row" style="margin: var(--spacing-large) 0; background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color); border-radius: 4px;">
