    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="overview" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. Executive Summary</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">This document provides a phased, step-by-step plan to migrate Comserv's production databases from a bare-metal server (192.168.1.198) to the existing Kubernetes cluster (VM ID 101 on Dell R710) using a dual-database sync strategy for zero-downtime cutover, enabling:</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>High Availability</strong>: Multi-node database cluster with automatic failover</li>
                <li><strong>Load Balancing</strong>: Read replicas and connection pooling via Kubernetes services</li>
                <li><strong>Zero Downtime</strong>: Blue-green deployment strategy during cutover</li>
                <li><strong>Scalability</strong>: Dynamic resource allocation and auto-healing</li>
                <li><strong>Simplified Operations</strong>: Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC) with GitOps workflow</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

